race.description: Avis Ballarat And Western Victoria Handicap (Bm56)
race.comment: DANCING JUICE (4) kicked off this campaign with a win two runs ago. Not as effective last time out when fifth over 1500m at Mornington, beaten 3.5 lengths. This doesn't look as hard so he can make amends. ABERLUTELY (9) travelled in a rearwards position then picked up fairly well in the straight and finished 3.5 lengths away in sixth last time out over 1500m at Mornington when resuming from a spell. Tackles a longer journey this time. Right in the mix. SUBTLE POWER (3) returned from a spell three weeks ago when she was prominent at the turn before being beaten 5 lengths into eighth over 1400m at Pakenham. Finds an easier assignment and can get the job done. LAYBUY (11) was last at the races when he finished seventh over 1800m at Kerang on April 19. Generally takes a run or two to hit his best but a wet track would bring him right into it.
